Set version to 1.6.1, update ChangeLog.

Fix assertion failures when object contains NaN.

(NaN == NaN) evaluates to False, which causes assertion failures when checking
for reference consistency in JSONValues.

Since we're checking for logical equivalency and not arithmetic equality, "is"
operator should be used instead of "==".

https://github.com/avian2/jsonmerge/issues/39.
Make metadataSchema work with local $refs.
Update README with info about merge_options.

Remove "meta" argument throughout the code.

The "meta" argument was just a special case cludge to pass an option to the
version strategy and had to be passed explicitly throughout most of the code.
mergeOptions is a better and more general way for doing this,

With this change, version strategy gets two new mergeOptions: metadata and
metadataSchema. They behave exactly like the meta arguments did to the
Merger.merge() and Merger.get_schema() methods.

To allow for the use case where a different metadata needs to be passed to each
merge()/get_schema() call without changing the schema, the new merge_options
argument adds global options to strategies.

Extract out get_key() from ArrayMergeById.merge()
